You definitely do get the
equations, which I'll show you

00:07:10.760 --> 00:07:12.880
in the not too far future.

00:07:12.880 --> 00:07:14.510
This intersection would
look something like this.

00:07:14.510 --> 00:07:16.400
I think you can
visualize it right now.

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:17.490
It would look
something like this.

00:07:20.950 --> 00:07:24.120
And if you were to look
straight down on this plane, if

00:07:24.120 --> 00:07:27.200
you were to look right above
the plane, this would look

00:07:27.200 --> 00:07:29.440
something-- this figure I
just drew in purple-- would

00:07:29.440 --> 00:07:30.410
look something like this.

00:07:33.060 --> 00:07:34.290
Well, I didn't draw
it that well.

00:07:34.290 --> 00:07:35.290
It'd be an ellipse.

00:07:35.290 --> 00:07:36.800
You know what an
ellipse looks like.

