00:08:49.390 --> 00:08:51.050
And there you get
your parabola.

00:08:51.050 --> 00:08:51.860
So that's interesting.

00:08:51.860 --> 00:08:54.830
If you keep kind of tilting--
if you start with a

00:08:54.830 --> 00:08:57.530
circle, tilt a little bit,
you get an ellipse.

00:08:57.530 --> 00:09:00.695
You get kind of a more
and more skewed ellipse.

00:09:00.695 --> 00:09:04.350
And at some point, the ellipse
keeps getting more and

00:09:04.350 --> 00:09:05.160
more skewed like that.

00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:10.660
It kind of pops right when you
become exactly parallel to

00:09:10.660 --> 00:09:11.990
the side of this top cone.

